description:
&#8220;I think the reason he calls it KickBack is because when he showed it to me I fell over backwards.&#8221; 
- <strong>Mac King</strong>

	&#8220;A great effect. Ryan has developed a truly righteous card trick, with a slap in the face ending!&#8221; 
- <strong>Aaron Fisher</strong>

	&#8220;If you don&#8217;t learn and start performing KickBack, then you&#8217;re a sucker.&#8221; 
- <strong>Lee Asher</strong>

	&#8220;KickBack is by far one of my all-time favorite sandwich effects to perform on both laymen and magicians alike.&#8221; 
- <strong>Luke Dancy</strong>

	&#8220;An instant classic. Few tricks hit people as hard as KickBack. It went straight into my &#8216;killer&#8217; file.&#8221; 
- <strong>R. Paul Wilson, from Court TV&#8217;s &#8220;Takedown&#8221;</strong>

	&#8220;Ryan&#8217;s KickBack does exactly that to your audience-it &#8216;kicks&#8217; their head back with the surprise ending.  I have been using this for the past few years and it has become a permanent part of my repertoire.  It is the strongest card trick in years and is perfect for <span class="caps">ANY</span> performing situation.&#8221; 
- <strong>Chris Korn, from A&#38;E&#8217;s &#8220;Mondo Magic&#8221;</strong>

	&#8220;Great visual magic!&#8221; 
- <strong>Bill Malone</strong>

	&#8220;KickBack is simply one of the best new card effects of this generation.&#8221; 
- <strong>David Regal</strong>

	&#8220;KickBack is diabolical, devilish, and wicked!&#8221; 
- <strong>J.B. Benn, from A&#38;E&#8217;s &#8220;Mondo Magic&#8221;</strong>

	&#8220;Quick and sharp- the ending is a truly magical experience not to be missed!&#8221; 
- <strong>Sebastian Clergue</strong>

	<strong><span class="caps">EFFECT</span></strong>: Start by placing two Aces off to the side.  Two spectators each select a card and replace their cards back in the deck.  The magician inserts the two Aces face-up into the deck and then <span class="caps">IMMEDIATELY</span>, spreads the deck to reveal two cards between the face-up Aces.  The spectators remove the &#8220;sandwiched&#8221; cards and those <span class="caps">ARE THE TWO ACES</span>!  the cards in the magician&#8217;s hands <span class="caps">ARE THE TWO SELECTIONS</span>!  <span class="caps">EXTREMELY VISUAL</span>!  <span class="caps">EASY TO DO</span>!

	This booklet describes the original version of KickBack along with updated handlings from <strong>Ryan Swigert</strong>, <strong>Chris Korn</strong>, and <strong>R. Paul Wilson</strong>. Learn how to perform this Underground hit with signed selections, with a borrowed deck, and even with different colored backs.

	(Gimmick cards, which are needed for some versions, are included!)
